why won't my week old sleep my week old daughter won't sleep at all during the day and is awake for anything up to hours at a time i have read that newborns are supposed to sleep for up to hours during the day but i can't get her to sleep it is now also starting to affect the night time sleep too and she is constantly restless and wakes throughout the night i am exhausted and can't get her to sleep she is tired too and is fighting herself to fall asleep i have tried putting her down in her cot and letting her cry herself to sleep but she cries until she chokes and i have to pick her up she wont sleep anywhere cot bed sling rocker chair nowhere has anyone experienced this please help doctor is on holiday until for the next two weeks so won't be seeing her until then please help thanks she is bottle fed and is drinking up to mils per feed and is very content after drinking she falls asleep after a feed but when i put her down she awakes five to ten minutes later and wont go back down have tried patting shushing etc and not picking her up but again she cries until she chokes and i have to pick her up also have tried infacol and gripe water this made her ten times worse she is currently on gaviscon infant for gastro reflux but its not helping will make app to see second doc asap my daughter was the same way she barely slept but she was also very fussy and cried off and on in the evenings turned out she has silent reflux and it took us about weeks to figure out why she wasn't sleeping it's uncomfortable for babies with reflux so they're known for not sleeping much there's a link below to see if your daughter may have any of the symptoms if so being that your doctor is out of town you could try calling one of the nurses and ask them what the proper dose of maalox would be for your daughter the night before we figured out what was wrong with my daughter she had only slept maybe or hours the entire day and she got almost hyper from lack of sleep i called the after hours nurse and she said it's not normal for a baby to not sleep and told me to get some maalox and give her some of that and see if it helped at that age letting her cry won't do any good she's too young to soothe herself to sleep but i understand having to do it i had to get away from my daughter after days of that and i would just go and take a hot shower just to have some peace and my husband would take her if you have anyone that can help you during the day so you can get a little sleep for me i knew something was wrong and i was going back to work after weeks so i needed to solve it before then if you suspect it could be reflux keep her elevated for at least minutes after a feeding and keep her head elevated while she sleeps the doctor told us we could give our daughter the maalox times a day for our daughter that didn't help and we did end up having to put her on prevacid solutabs which have helped immensely is there any other doctor in the office that could see your daughter i know at our pediatrician's office they have other doctor's cover when ours is off on vacation or has a day off does she sleep if you hold her i spent weeks holding my daughter and sleeping on the couch just so i could get some sleep do what you have to to get some sleep till you can get back to the doctor good luck gripe water may also help a little it helped with my daughter's fussiness and gas that sometimes comes with having reflux Urinary incontinence Breastfeeding Knots Landing Milton H. Erickson The Catcher in the Rye Sleep EastEnders Insomnia Humphrey Bogart The Contender (television series) Sin City Freddy's Dead: The Final Nightmare Soap opera Social rule Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Childbirth Michael Garibaldi Shaggy dog story Narcolepsy Hypoglycemia Gastroesophageal reflux disease Apollo 8 The Shining (film) Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) The Amber Spyglass Daylight saving time W.I.T.C.H. Infant Elvis Presley Saturday Night Live Otello Pitaten One Tree Hill (TV series) The Marshall Ma